Kea - Dev Repo
curl -1sLf 'https://dl.cloudsmith.io/public/isc/kea-dev/cfg/setup/bash.deb.sh' | sudo bash
apt install isc-kea


Stork
# /etc/stork/server.env
curl -1sLf 'https://dl.cloudsmith.io/public/isc/stork/cfg/setup/bash.deb.sh' | sudo bash
apt install isc-stork-server
stork-tool db-create --db-name stork --db-user stork
# This password needs to be copied into the server environment file or used in the stork-server command line, to configure the server to use this password while connecting to the database.


systemctl enable isc-stork-server
systemctl start isc-stork-server
systemctl status isc-stork-server

Notes
- Stork Server does not read the /etc/stork/server.env by default when calling the binary directly (not using systemd). 
isc-kea-dhcp4 — Kea DHCPv4 server package
isc-kea-dhcp6 — Kea DHCPv6 server package
isc-kea-dhcp-ddns — Kea DHCP DDNS server
isc-kea-ctrl-agent — Kea Control Agent for remote configuration
isc-kea-admin — Kea database administration tools
isc-kea-hooks — Kea open source DHCP hooks


